result.execSummary:
The defendant Stephanee Jean Ward was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Theft-Movable Property >$2500-$5000, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 11:16 Defendant Stephanee Jean Ward in court with attorney Liesl E. Nelson.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 14CF214 heard at this time. OSullivan: guilty to Ct#1 and Ct#2 in 14CF196 and dismiss Ct#3 and Ct#4 but read in for restitution and sentencing purposes. Dismiss 14CF214. Nelson and Def agree.   Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant. Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def pleas guilty to Ct#1 and Ct#2 in 14CF196; Nelson stipulates to a factual basis.   COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS.  Court finds and adjudicates Def guilty of Ct#1 and Ct#2 in 14CF196. Dismisses Ct#3 and Ct#4 but will read in for restitution purposes OSullivan addresses sentencing and asks for 45 days conditional jail time and 30 days for restitution. Kenneth, Tara and Elizabeth McNiff address the court. Nelson addresses sentencing; disagrees with jail time and requests expungement. Def addresses the court. Court: S/W 4 years probation on each count; concurrent. conditions: restitution TBD in 30 days, court costs, agent to look at mental health evaluation, DNA sample and surcharge on Ct#1, expungement available upon successful completion of probation, 5 days conditional jail time stayed until no later than September 14, 2015 at 7pm. Huber is allowed.  Dismiss 14CF214.  OSullivan to prepare new information with just Ct#1 and Ct#2 on 14CF196.  Appeal rights are given to the defendant.
Plea hearing at 07-14-2015 11:00 am.

4:25 14CF214 is also included.   Defendant Stephanee Jean Ward in court with attorney Liesl E. Nelson.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  There is not an agreement on this whole case at this time - attorneys feel this  is able to be resolved.  Judge- this can be set for plea mid to late July.
